shared_text:
Custer School District 16-1
May 20 at 5:19 PM ·

Custer School District meal deliveries have been extended throughout the summer. The meal delivery days and times have had to be adjusted.

Tuesdays and Thursdays: CES – Door C pick-up will go from 11:00am-11:20am. The Pringle (11:15am) and 4-Mile (12:00pm) deliveries will remain the same. The intersection of Highway 385 & Highway 16 delivery will be from 11:45am-12:00pm. Aspen View will be from 12:10pm-12:30pm. Triple T will be from 12:45pm-1:00pm. There will no longer be an armory delivery. Those wanting meals will need to come to the drop-off points at the new times. Students will still get breakfasts and lunches for 7 days a week but within the two deliveries instead of the three deliveries, we had been doing each week. Thank you. Have a great summer!

Members of the Black Hills Conference have decided to become a part of the Be the Light Campaign this Thursday evening to honor numerous groups during this pandemic.

We, the Black Hills Conference, invite you and your community to join us at 8:20 on Thursday, April 16, for 20 minutes by turning on your stadium lights.

Let's let our those who are on the front lines and our senior know we have appreciate them and that they are not forgotten.

The Edgemont Moguls will be participating.

Attention all CSD Families ~ Due to the forecasted weather, the Custer School District will move the April 2nd homework packet pick-up and drop-off to Monday, April 6th from 6:30am to 2pm. CES pick up will be curbside at the main door on the east side of the building. The Jr/Sr High School will be the same as it was previously. And, Hermosa School will be curbside pick-up as planned.

FYI – A SchoolMessenger announcement is scheduled to go out to all families and staff tonight at 7:40 p.m. regarding this same information.
